{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Collecting more training data as a huge language repository can allow MT models to internally learn relevant linguistic knowledge.",
    "Lastly, we propose the use of a recently introduced paradigm namely pre-training-fine-tuning in MT model design.",
    "By leveraging the transformer architecture (Vaswani et al., 2017) and a vast amount of training data, commercial MT developers can first pre-train a large language model (LLM) to better learn linguistic patterns and statistical laws at the lexical, syntactic, and even semantic levels.",
    "The LLM, as a generalpurpose language model, can then be fine-tuned and optimized for specific translation tasks.",
    "The present study attempts to examine whether the simplification universal observed in human translations also holds true for machine translations and whether the variable genre a significant impact on the simplification features."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "By leveraging the transformer architecture (Vaswani et al., 2017) and a vast amount of training data, commercial MT developers can first pre-train a large language model (LLM) to better learn linguistic patterns and statistical laws at the lexical, syntactic, and even semantic levels."
